title: Republican vote-auditing efforts face another setback in Arizona.
description: A judge in Cochise County ruled that local officials did not follow state law in planning to hand-count ballots in this week’s election.
dc:creator: Charles Homans

media:content.media:credit: Paul Ratje for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Bisbee, Ariz., the county seat of Cochise County, which had a plan to hand-count its ballots for this year’s elections.
